-- Turkey Stocks: Garanti, Tekfen, Yapi Are Active in Istanbul
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-01-18T16:42:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-18/turkey-stocks-garanti-tekfen-yapi-are-active-in-istanbul.html
Turkey ’s benchmark ISE National 100
Index rose for a third day, adding 1.6 percent to 54,384.76, its
highest since Dec. 7, at the close in Istanbul.  The following stocks were active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  Tekfen Holding AS (TKFEN TI), a builder, added 3 percent to
5.52 liras, the highest since Dec. 21. The company was rated
“buy” with a price estimate of 8.3 liras in new coverage at
 UniCredit SpA. (UCG)   Turkiye Garanti Bankasi AS (GARAN TI), Turkey’s largest
listed bank by market value, jumped 4.7 percent to 6.24 liras,
extending its three-day advance to 10 percent and leading gains
on the Turkish market as emerging-market stocks climbed to a
two-month high on speculation  Greece  was nearing a deal to write
down debt. Yapi & Kredi Bankasi AS (YKBNK TI) rose 2.5 percent
to 2.90 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
